    "125339909": {
      "title": "Gravitation and Cosmology Principles and Applications of the General Theory of Relativity",
      "abstract": "Steven Weinberg Chichester: Wiley 1972 pp xxviii + 657 price £8.50 The last ten years, beginning with the excitement resulting from the discovery of quasars, have seen a remarkable recrudescence of interest in general relativity, particularly in its astrophysical applications. Although the most recent laboratory investigations on the existence of gravitational waves have failed to corroborate the claims made by Professor Weber of the University of Maryland, the era of experimental general relativity has undoubtedly begun, with the object of discriminating between Einstein's and alternative theories of gravitation, such as Dicke's."
